data.name: T9
data.description:
Make a simple T9(predictive text) for you phone. The function has 2 arguments, a string which is user's word and an array with over 500 random words. Your task is to return an array of the possible words that the user miswritten. All the characters of the string is included in the array's word. (The orded of the characters doesn't matter)

If the string is larger than array's word then don't return it.

Example :

    string = "de"     # it won't matter if it was "ed"
  
    array = ["dog", "deer", "deal"]
You should return
  
      ['deer', 'deal']
  
  Because "dog" hasn't an "e" in it.
  
 Note : If the string or the array is empty: return []
